{
  "texts": [
    "At the heart of its efficiency is an out-of-core approach to model merging.",
    "By loading only the tensors necessary for each individual operation into working memory, MergeKit can scale from a high-end research cluster all the way down to a personal laptop with no GPU and limited Random-Access Memory (RAM).",
    "We use Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) approach to optimize the merging process for large models.",
    "The DAG structure allows for efficient computation by organizing operations in a way that minimizes redundancy and resource usage.",
    "This method is particularly advantageous in handling model merging on resource-constrained environments."
  ]
}